{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Plan how immutability enforcement below individual writers will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["f2bb5fda9fe912bdd"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"immutability enforcement below individual writers"},{"coaching":"Pin down unknown projection contract across child stories with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f93e1c06c2f62b2e4"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"unknown projection contract across child stories"},{"coaching":"Propagate the revision for documentation ownership gap across child stories to the child tickets.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f2b7501aa16db6db2"],"move_id":"11","move_name":"propagate to children","subject":"documentation ownership gap across child stories"},{"coaching":"Plan how bundled acceptance criterion for schema and projections will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f1f31f8979c74b9b8"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"bundled acceptance criterion for schema and projections"},{"coaching":"Plan how overlapping compaction test suite coverage will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f681754b96c5d1b9c"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"overlapping compaction test suite coverage"},{"coaching":"Test the riskiest assumption behind const-true JSON Schema handler in gen_types first.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f9ebd0d9a8c2c371f"],"move_id":"4","move_name":"riskiest-assumption test","subject":"const-true JSON Schema handler in gen_types"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":5,"blocking":1,"dropped":12,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":12,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","ran":true,"references":0,"resolved":0,"status":"pass"},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":12,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":12914,"file_impact":8,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":3,"edges":3,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":12,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"pass","verify_commands_linted":4,"verify_lint_abstained":4},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":3245,"ran":true,"status":"pass","worst_parent_child_pair_tokens":5315},"P9":{"applicable":false,"blocking":false,"file_impact":8,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":280.2,"llm_calls":23,"llm_ms":671875.3,"total_ms":672309.9,"verify_requests":21},"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":true,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["G3","G4","G6","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","F1","F4","G5","T12","T2","T4","T5e","T7"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify in the Architecture Decisions (and in story 6fe2's _processors.py scope) that `process_edit` must explicitly skip `creation_channel` and `creation_channel_inferred` via a named immutable-field exclusion set, mirroring how `ticket_id` and `created_at` are never overwritten by EDIT, and add an AC-level test that an EDIT event carrying `fields.creation_channel` does not alter the compiled state.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'Reducer processors treat creation_channel as CREATE/SNAPSHOT-only state and ignore the key on every later mutation event, enforcing immutability below individual writers.'","Code: process_edit iterates data['fields'] and applies any key already present in state: `if field_name not in state: continue` then `state[field_name] = new_value`. No exclusion list exists.","ABSENCE: The plan does not specify that creation_channel or creation_channel_inferred must be added to a blocked-field set in process_edit, nor does any child story (6fe2's scope section or file_impact list) mention modifying process_edit's field-guard logic."],"finding":"The plan asserts creation_channel is immutable after genesis ('Reducer processors treat creation_channel as CREATE/SNAPSHOT-only state and ignore the key on every later mutation event'), but the existing process_edit in _processors.py applies any field already in state when it appears in EDIT.fields (line 494: `if field_name not in state: continue`). Since process_create will add creation_channel (and conditionally creation_channel_inferred) to state, a subsequent EDIT event containing fields.creation_channel will silently overwrite genesis provenance. The plan never specifies that process_edit must have an explicit named exclusion for these keys — only that mutation events 'ignore the key', which is true for specialized processors (LINK, STATUS, JIRA_BIND) but is NOT automatically true for the general-purpose process_edit without an explicit guard.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2bb5fda9fe912bdd","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section ('Reducer processors treat creation_channel as CREATE/SNAPSHOT-only state and ignore the key on every later mutation event'); src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py lines 485-510","norm_id":"n4289d61664b4bf81","priority":0.85,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["A crafted or buggy EDIT event with data.fields.creation_channel='mcp' is replayed against a ticket created via cli — process_edit overwrites the genesis channel, defeating the immutability guarantee.","An older rebar version that does not know about creation_channel emits a general EDIT event that happens to include a creation_channel key (e.g., from a schema migration tool) — the channel is silently rewritten."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"In _processors.py, add a module-level frozenset: `_IMMUTABLE_FIELDS = frozenset({'creation_channel', 'creation_channel_inferred'})` and add `if field_name in _IMMUTABLE_FIELDS: continue` inside the process_edit loop before the general assignment. Reference this constant from the plan's Architecture Decisions section.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"medium","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Align 6fe2 and e622 on the legacy missing-field projection contract: either (a) 6fe2's reducer leaves creation_channel absent for missing-field CREATEs (and the unknown output in 6fe2 AC4 is produced by e622's inference helper on mismatch), or (b) the no-op guard in e622's helper checks for None/absent rather than any presence of the key — and update both ACs and the helper spec accordingly.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4","G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["6fe2 AC4: 'a legacy CREATE with no channel reduces to unknown without creation_channel_inferred'","e622 What: 'It is a no-op when state already has creation_channel; otherwise it reads state[\"ticket_id\"]...'","Parent architecture: 'Historical records without the field project jira only when all creation-stable signals agree' (implies field must be absent, not unknown, for inference to run)","If 6fe2 sets creation_channel=unknown in compiled_state, then e622's no-op guard fires on that value and Jira inference is blocked for ALL legacy records regardless of the three-signal predicate","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Child 6fe2 AC4 claims that 'a legacy CREATE with no channel reduces to unknown without creation_channel_inferred,' implying the reducer writes creation_channel=unknown into compiled state. Child e622 defines _project_legacy_creation_channel as 'a no-op when state already has creation_channel.' If 6fe2's reducer sets creation_channel=unknown for missing-field legacy CREATEs, e622's helper will always be a no-op for those records, blocking Jira inference from ever firing on full-log replay. The two children cannot both be correct as written: either 6fe2 sets unknown (which blocks e622's inference) or 6fe2 leaves the field absent (which means 6fe2 AC4's 'reduces to unknown' is not verifiable at 6fe2's own delivery boundary, before e622 exists).","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f93e1c06c2f62b2e4","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 AC4; child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 What (_project_legacy_creation_channel no-op guard)","norm_id":"nae1fde64f234f78e","priority":0.5025,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A legacy Jira ticket with jira-* ID, reconciler author, reconciler env_id is processed by the full stack after both 6fe2 and e622 land: 6fe2's reducer writes unknown into compiled_state; e622's helper sees creation_channel='unknown' (a present value), declares no-op, and the ticket is never labeled jira+inferred — violating parent AC5 and e622 AC5.","During 6fe2's delivery, AC4 test '-k legacy' runs before e622 exists: if 6fe2 leaves the field absent (to allow future inference), the test expecting 'unknown' fails; if 6fe2 sets unknown, the test passes but blocks e622's inference later."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Define the contract explicitly: 6fe2's reducer does NOT write creation_channel into compiled_state when the CREATE event has no creation_channel field (i.e., field remains absent from state dict). e622's _project_legacy_creation_channel is the sole writer for legacy records (setting jira+inferred on match, unknown on mismatch). Update 6fe2 AC4 to say 'a legacy CREATE with no channel is left without creation_channel until the inference helper runs, which then projects unknown for non-Jira records without an inferred marker.' This keeps the no-op guard meaningful (it guards against re-inference of already-resolved state, including recorded channels and post-e622 unknown outputs).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Assign explicit ownership of the 'diagnostic trust boundary' documentation statement (creation_channel_inferred is diagnostic metadata, not a security attestation) to one child — most naturally e622 alongside its inference documentation — and add a corresponding assertion to test_schema_coverage.py or the docs AC proof command.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent SC5: 'The public schema and documentation define the vocabulary, default/fallback semantics, import behavior, and diagnostic trust boundary.'","Parent architecture: 'It is diagnostic metadata, not a security attestation.'","6fe2 docs scope: 'local channel contract' — no mention of trust boundary.","e622 docs scope: 'Document recorded versus inferred Jira provenance and the import/source_* distinction' — no mention of trust boundary.","568c docs scope: 'SNAPSHOT-only replay plus snapshot rebuild emit the same creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred values' — no mention of trust boundary.","No child AC cites test_schema_coverage.py checking for diagnostic/security-attestation language in any docs file.","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Parent Success Criterion 5 requires that 'The public schema and documentation define the vocabulary, default/fallback semantics, import behavior, and diagnostic trust boundary.' No child explicitly commits to documenting the 'diagnostic trust boundary' — that creation_channel_inferred is diagnostic metadata, not a security attestation — in any named documentation deliverable or acceptance criterion.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2b7501aa16db6db2","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"Parent SC5; child 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 docs scope; child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 docs scope; child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 docs scope","norm_id":"n11032a777d7ad65d","priority":0.4857,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An auditor or security reviewer reads the generated docs and concludes that creation_channel_inferred=true is a verified/cryptographic claim about channel authenticity rather than an inference heuristic — because no documentation explicitly states the diagnostic-only trust boundary.","test_schema_coverage.py passes without asserting that docs contain the trust-boundary language, leaving the parent SC5 verification incomplete."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add to e622's documentation scope: 'Note in docs/output-schemas.md that creation_channel_inferred is diagnostic metadata, not a security attestation, and cannot be used to verify channel authenticity.' Extend test_schema_coverage.py to assert this language (or a canonical equivalent) appears in the relevant doc.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5714,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Split acceptance criterion #6 into two or more focused criteria: one for JSON schema + generated types (schema_ticket_state, schema_outputs, gen_types --check) and one for runtime projections + NDJSON export, each with its own proof command.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["F1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["The proof command chains: 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/facades/test_creation_channel.py -k projections tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py && python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check'","Five logically distinct surfaces (JSON schema, type generation, show projection, list/search projection, NDJSON export) are collapsed into one pass/fail criterion."],"finding":"Acceptance criterion #6 bundles five distinct verifiable sub-outcomes (TicketState schemas, generated types, runtime show/list/search projections, exported NDJSON, and gen_types --check) into a single criterion, making it harder to attribute a failure to a specific deliverable and stretching the 'coherent single-outcome' F1 requirement.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f1f31f8979c74b9b8","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — criterion 6: 'TicketState schemas, generated types, runtime show/list/search projections, plus exported NDJSON expose the six-value enum...'","norm_id":"na6acb4dc37e8d05c","priority":0.3143,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A test failure in test_schema_outputs.py is obscured by the compound command, requiring the executor to re-run individual files to locate the broken sub-surface.","A partial implementation that passes schema and type checks but misses the NDJSON export field is still reported as a failing combined criterion with no clear attribution."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7143,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Differentiate AC #7 and AC #8's verify commands so each targets a non-overlapping -k filter within test_creation_channel_compaction.py — e.g., keep AC #7's '-k \"recorded or inferred or rollback_recovery\"' and restrict AC #8 to '-k \"legacy_snapshot or snapshot_only_replay or partial_horizon or rebuild\"' to make each AC independently falsifiable.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC #7 verify: 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k \"recorded or inferred or rollback_recovery\"'","AC #8 verify: 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_snapshot.py' — no -k filter, so it runs all tests in the file, including those covered by AC #7's filter."],"finding":"AC #7 and AC #8 both execute tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py — AC #8 runs it without a -k filter (a superset of AC #7's '-k \"recorded or inferred or rollback_recovery\"'), making AC #7's verify command a strict subset of AC #8's, constituting a near-duplicate verification overlap.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f681754b96c5d1b9c","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC #7 ('Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k \"recorded or inferred or rollback_recovery\"'); AC #8 ('Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_snapshot.py')","norm_id":"n4b422eb6b18122f2","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["At review time, both ACs are marked done by pointing to the same test run; the distinction between 'compaction durability' (AC #7) and 'legacy-SNAPSHOT/rebuild scenarios' (AC #8) is lost, making it unclear which scenarios each AC is independently gating."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7143,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a `\"const\"` branch to `gen_types._pytype()` (emitting `Literal[<value>]`) as a prerequisite within story 6fe2, and note this in the epic plan's AC or Architecture Decisions so the dependency is visible to reviewers without reading child-ticket comments.","cohort":["T3"],"criteria":["T3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'ticket_state.schema.json encodes that rule formally as {\"const\": true}'","AC proof command: 'python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check'","Code inspection of gen_types.py _pytype(): handles '$ref', 'enum', list-type, 'array', 'object', None — no 'const' branch exists","Child ticket 6fe2 comment: 'gen_types._pytype has no const handler -> will add const->Literal[True] so creation_channel_inferred renders correctly and gen_types --check passes' — acknowledges the gap but the epic plan does not flag it as a prerequisite","Evidence class: Verified (observed via code inspection)"],"finding":"The epic plan cites `python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check` as a passing acceptance-criterion proof command, but the `gen_types._pytype()` function has no handler for the JSON Schema `{\"const\": true}` keyword that the plan uses to encode `creation_channel_inferred`. Without adding a `const` branch, `_pytype` will fall through to the `jtype == None` arm and emit `Any` instead of `Literal[True]`, causing `--check` to fail on the generated diff.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9ebd0d9a8c2c371f","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC line 5 (`python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check`); Architecture Decisions section ('ticket_state.schema.json encodes that rule formally as {\"const\": true}'); src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py `_pytype()` method (lines 115–149)","norm_id":"n6de4ca00454c7604","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Story 6fe2 implementer adds `creation_channel_inferred` to the schema with `{\"const\": true}` but forgets to extend gen_types._pytype — `--check` fails in CI, blocking the story.","Even if the implementer remembers, the epic plan's AC reads as if `--check` will pass out-of-box, misleading reviewers who gate on the epic AC rather than the child's comment."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In `gen_types._pytype()`, add before the `jtype = node.get('type')` line: `if 'const' in node: self._used_typing.add('Literal'); return f\"Literal[{node['const']!r}]\"`. Then add a sentence to the epic Architecture Decisions or the AC note: 'gen_types must handle {\"const\": true} → Literal[True] before --check can pass; this is a prerequisite within story 6fe2.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] State the values (or source module) of REBAR_AUTHOR and REBAR_ENV_ID explicitly in the Architecture Decisions section, analogous to how LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR and LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID are defined as exact literals.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Missing/None signals or legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides intentionally project unknown.'","LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR and LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID are explicitly defined as exact literals in the plan, but REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID receive no analogous definition.","The executor must know the exact values/module of REBAR_AUTHOR and REBAR_ENV_ID to code the override-detection branch in inbound_translate._event_meta."],"finding":"The plan references REBAR_AUTHOR and REBAR_ENV_ID as existing constants that trigger 'unknown' projection for legacy events, but does not define their values, types, or source module within this plan, leaving the executor unable to implement the inference branch without out-of-band knowledge.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fcf0c46b8e2cee5c1","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — inference paragraph: 'Missing/None signals or legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides intentionally project unknown.'","norm_id":"nd644169d576e96a6","priority":0.099,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Executor implements the inference logic and cannot determine what values constitute a REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID override, potentially conflating them with the legacy Jira signals or missing the branch entirely."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence such as: 'REBAR_AUTHOR and REBAR_ENV_ID are the existing override constants from src/rebar/reducer/_version.py (values: \"rebar\" and \"rebar\" respectively — or whatever the actual literals are); events whose author or env_id match these are not eligible for Jira inference and project unknown.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify explicitly in the Architecture Decisions whether creation_channel is a required parameter on create_core (with no default) or carries a stated fallback (e.g. 'unknown' is forbidden for new writes; the parameter is required and the validator enforces a non-unknown concrete value at runtime).","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'New writes always record a concrete non-unknown value.' — implies no default of unknown for new writes, but does not say whether create_core enforces this via a required parameter or via a validated default.","The plan names 'every create_core call site' in Risks but does not specify what create_core does if called without the argument (raise? default to unknown? default to python?)."],"finding":"The plan does not specify whether the new creation_channel parameter to create_core is required or has a default fallback value, leaving the executor uncertain how to handle any internal callers not yet updated to supply the channel.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fbe0f6bc4460b3ee8","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Every live producer declares its channel at its entry boundary. Local create_core callers plus the direct Jira CREATE seam use the shared runtime validator before writing; the core does not inspect the call stack.'","norm_id":"nd5c7426bc86e89c2","priority":0.066,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An executor adds creation_channel as an optional parameter defaulting to 'unknown' to preserve backward compat with internal helpers, violating the 'new writes always record a concrete non-unknown value' invariant.","An executor makes it required, breaking untracked internal callers not covered by the enumerated entry-boundary list."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add: 'creation_channel is a required positional-or-keyword parameter on create_core with no default; passing an unrecognized or missing value raises a ValueError at the runtime validator. Entry-boundary callers that have not yet been updated to supply the channel will fail loudly rather than silently recording unknown.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an Acceptance Criterion covering the spec-load contract test for inbound_translate._event_meta's late-import of LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR/LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID, e.g. 'Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_import_isolation.py (or equivalent) that spec-load succeeds and the late-import pattern does not create circular or context-dependent import failures.'","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'inbound_translate._event_meta performs the absolute package import ... inside its function body, following the module's established late-import pattern, and the reducer imports the same symbols normally. This does not depend on sibling reconciler package context and is pinned by an isolated spec-load contract test.'","No AC verify command references a spec-load or import-isolation contract test file; AC #5 references tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py -k legacy, which tests inference behavior, not import-time module isolation."],"finding":"The Architecture Decisions section specifies 'an isolated spec-load contract test' as a pinned deliverable to verify the late-import pattern in inbound_translate._event_meta, but no Acceptance Criterion covers the existence or passage of this test — it is an uncovered deliverable.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7c05466a2a371337","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions (paragraph 3: 'pinned by an isolated spec-load contract test'); Acceptance Criteria section (all ACs)","norm_id":"nd5aefbe669592357","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An implementer writes the late-import pattern but omits or misconfigures the contract test; no AC fails to catch the omission, leaving a broken import pattern undetected under spec-load conditions."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add an AC: 'The isolated spec-load contract test for inbound_translate._event_meta's late import of LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR and LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID passes in isolation from the reconciler package context. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_import_isolation.py.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Strengthen AC #4 to explicitly require a test case verifying that an imported NDJSON record carrying a creation_channel field (e.g. 'cli') results in the local ticket recording 'import', not the source value, e.g. add '-k \"import or source_channel_not_inherited\"' or name the sub-case explicitly.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Import creates a new local ticket through the import channel. Existing source_id, source_created_at, source_author, and source_env continue to describe the source record; an exported source creation_channel is not reused as the new local channel.'","AC #4: 'NDJSON import reports import while retaining source_* record provenance. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/io/test_creation_channel.py -k import.' — the -k filter 'import' does not specify a sub-case that tests the non-reuse of an incoming creation_channel value."],"finding":"Architecture Decisions explicitly states 'an exported source creation_channel is not reused as the new local channel' as a behavioral rule for NDJSON import, but AC #4's verify command ('uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/io/test_creation_channel.py -k import') does not name or require a test case for this non-reuse rule, leaving it potentially uncovered.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb5e27afc5aebbabb","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions (paragraph 5: 'an exported source creation_channel is not reused as the new local channel'); AC #4","norm_id":"nfda3928bf782471f","priority":0.1257,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An input NDJSON containing a creation_channel of 'cli' or 'python' is imported; the importer copies that value rather than setting 'import'; AC #4 passes if the test only checks that the output is 'import' for a clean fixture but does not exercise the non-reuse guard with a poisoned-channel fixture."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Amend AC #4 to: 'NDJSON import reports import while retaining source_* record provenance; an incoming creation_channel value in the source NDJSON is not propagated to the new local ticket. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/io/test_creation_channel.py -k \"import or source_channel_not_inherited\".'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the concrete mechanism for capturing affected ticket IDs after a compaction-pause violation (e.g., a query against the event store for SNAPSHOT events written in the downgrade window, a compaction-activity log path, or a rebar CLI subcommand) so the compensating-forward rebuild is fully actionable.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"record affected IDs from the downgrade-window compaction activity, re-deploy the new binary, and rebuild those snapshots from the full log with rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log/include_retired\"","The plan specifies the recovery action but not the mechanism for reliably identifying which IDs were compacted during the violation window.","T4 criterion: 'The remedy is an explicit rollback/back-out plan or expand-contract — acknowledgement alone is insufficient.'"],"finding":"The compaction-pause-violation recovery path says 'record affected IDs from the downgrade-window compaction activity' but does not specify the mechanism by which those IDs are captured — no log query, no event-store scan command, no audit trail reference — leaving the rollback remedy partially underspecified for a destructive (irreversible compaction) scenario.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc50d94995e687f20","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback matrix paragraph; Risks and Mitigations — 'Snapshot omission/recovery'; AC for docs/concurrency.md","norm_id":"nbd43051a78f67229","priority":0.2513,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An operator violates the compaction pause during a downgrade window; without a prescribed scan command or audit log query, they cannot reliably enumerate affected ticket IDs and may miss some, leaving provenance silently absent from those SNAPSHOTs."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add to the rollback description: 'Query the event store for all SNAPSHOT events whose compacted_at timestamp falls within the downgrade window (e.g., `rebar events list --type SNAPSHOT --since <deploy-old> --until <redeploy-new>`) to enumerate affected IDs before running rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log.' Also add this to the docs/concurrency.md AC content requirement.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a CHANGELOG entry and/or Python library API documentation update to the plan's documentation scope, covering the new creation_channel parameter, its default value, and the closed vocabulary.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"Direct public Python calls default to python\" — this is a new parameter visible to Python library consumers.","The AC lists docs/event-schema.md, docs/output-schemas.md, and docs/concurrency.md but not a CHANGELOG or library API reference update.","ABSENCE: no mention of CHANGELOG, API reference, or library release notes anywhere in the plan."],"finding":"The plan introduces creation_channel as a new keyword parameter (defaulting to python) at the create_core call boundary, which is a new public Python library API surface, but no CHANGELOG entry or Python library API documentation update is mentioned anywhere in the plan.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f037ea4f8c573853a","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Every live producer declares its channel at its entry boundary'; Scope IN; Success Criteria","norm_id":"n0156bb2315953ce2","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A Python library consumer calling create_core or a wrapper that previously accepted no channel argument now needs to know about the new parameter to intentionally override the default; without CHANGELOG or API docs, they discover this only by reading source code or encountering unexpected audit output."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Before finalising LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR and LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID, run a one-off corpus probe (e.g., a script that scans all CREATE events in the event store and reports distinct author/env_id/ticket_id-prefix combinations) to empirically confirm the three-signal predicate has zero false-positive and acceptable false-negative rates; record the findings in the plan or a linked note.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Define both constants in src/rebar/reducer/_version.py' — constants are named but their derivation from actual event corpus is not documented","'require the exact three-signal Jira predicate and add near-miss negative cases' — planned tests are synthetic fixtures, not corpus probes","'Missing/None signals or legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides intentionally project unknown' — safe fallback exists but does not eliminate the false-positive risk on the 'jira-' predicate branch","ABSENCE: no mention of running a query/grep against the actual event store to confirm the predicate uniquely identifies Jira-origin tickets before coding it in"],"finding":"The LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR ('reconciler') and LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID ('reconciler') constants used in the three-signal historical Jira inference predicate are asserted as correct but not derived from an empirical corpus probe. No spike or log-scan step is planned to verify precision (false-positive rate) and recall (false-negative rate) against real stored event data before these constants are committed to an immutable inference rule.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f40776a7bd68a2287","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Historical records without the field project jira only when all creation-stable signals agree'; Risks and Mitigations — 'False historical attribution'","norm_id":"na63798681200e7b0","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A legacy CLI-created ticket whose ticket_id happens to start with 'jira-' (e.g., from a manual import or naming collision) and whose author/env_id match the reconciler literals would be permanently and incorrectly labeled jira with creation_channel_inferred=true — an immutable misattribution.","The reconciler may have written events under different author/env strings during certain historical periods, causing real Jira-origin tickets to fall through to unknown — reducing audit value silently."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a throwaway spike script (e.g., scripts/probe_legacy_jira_signals.py) that scans the event store, groups CREATE events by (author, env_id, ticket_id_prefix), and emits a frequency table. Run it once pre-implementation, verify the predicate uniquely selects Jira-origin tickets, and record the corpus counts in a comment adjacent to the constant definitions in _version.py. This converts an asserted constant into a data-derived one and satisfies the T2 empirical-validation requirement.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.3333,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"no","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add at least a minimal runtime flag (e.g., `REBAR_CREATION_CHANNEL_ENABLED` env var defaulting to true) so operators can disable channel recording per-ingress without a full binary rollback while a defect is investigated.","cohort":["E3","T12"],"criteria":["T12"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"The MVP deliberately has no writer-only configuration switch or intermediate binary mode; attribution defects are recovered by pausing the affected creation ingress at the deployment boundary and rolling forward.\"","T12 criterion (a) requires a behavior change to reach production via flag/canary/staged rollout, not a single 100%-traffic flip."],"finding":"The plan explicitly rejects a staged rollout flag or binary mode, meaning the creation_channel behavior change reaches all traffic in a single flip with no canary or gradual exposure path.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd589229be992a9ba","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions (eighth bullet) and Risks and Mitigations (Compatibility bullet)","norm_id":"n5058c08612d11cc4","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A latent bug in the channel-selection logic (e.g., wrong default in create_core, missed call site) immediately affects all new tickets created after deployment with no ability to gate or roll back individual ingress paths."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Introduce a single boolean env/config gate (`REBAR_CREATION_CHANNEL_ENABLED=true`) checked at write time in create_core; if false, omit the field entirely (treating it as a legacy event). This gives a cheap per-deployment knob with no schema impact.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Document (in docs/concurrency.md and the AC for Story 568c) a scripted, end-to-end rollback runbook — including a command that enumerates all snapshots compacted during the downgrade window and bulk-invokes rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log — so the undo path is a single operator command, not a manual multi-step procedure.","cohort":["E3","T12"],"criteria":["T12"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"If that pause is violated, record affected IDs from the downgrade-window compaction activity, re-deploy the new binary, and rebuild those snapshots from the full log with rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log/include_retired\"","The rollback matrix has three distinct states requiring operator judgment to classify each ticket, plus manual invocation of rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log per affected ID.","T12 criterion (b) requires an explicit, cheap, tested way to undo quickly without data cleanup."],"finding":"The rollback path documented in the plan (stop compaction, capture affected IDs, re-deploy, rebuild snapshots) is multi-step and operationally expensive, violating the T12 requirement for a cheap and quick undo.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ffffa02714d71ef9d","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions (eighth bullet, rollback matrix) and Risks and Mitigations (Downgrade first-compaction omission bullet)","norm_id":"na7ecdbca2689c23b","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An operator performs a full binary downgrade without pre-stopping compaction (the plan calls this a 'pause violation'), then must manually enumerate affected snapshot IDs across the entire ticket store and trigger per-ticket rebuilds — a potentially hours-long recovery under production pressure."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a `rebar repair creation-channel --since <timestamp>` CLI subcommand (or a documented shell one-liner using existing tooling) that: (1) queries all tickets whose latest SNAPSHOT timestamp falls within a given window, (2) runs rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log on each, and (3) reports results. Reference this command in the rollback runbook so the undo path is one command with a known time bound.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit post-rollback schema-state assertion to the rollback matrix: state that after a full binary downgrade, SNAPSHOTs lack `creation_channel` but remain valid under the old schema (confirming old binary treats unknown keys permissively or that no old-binary required-field violation is triggered), and that the mixed log (new CREATEs + old SNAPSHOTs) is safe for old-binary reads until compensating-forward rebuild is complete.","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan says: 'a full downgrade to the immediately pre-feature binary hides the field' — this characterizes visibility, not schema state.","'an old-binary first compaction omits the field from its SNAPSHOT, but the creation-bearing CREATE remains permanently retained as .retired' — the intermediate mixed state (SNAPSHOT missing field, CREATE retaining it) is named but not asserted valid under old-binary schema expectations.","'If that pause is violated, re-upgrade and rebuild affected snapshots' — compensating-forward path described but post-rollback state before re-upgrade is not characterized.","The rubric requires: 'the plan must assert on the schema STATE AFTER rollback, not merely that rollback exits 0'"],"finding":"The rollback matrix describes the recovery PROCEDURE but never explicitly asserts the schema STATE of the system after a full binary downgrade completes — specifically whether SNAPSHOTs written by the old binary under the old schema are valid, whether a mixed log (new CREATEs with creation_channel + old-binary SNAPSHOTs without it) satisfies the old reader's invariants, and whether the compensating-forward rebuild leaves the system in a fully consistent state.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0dc28bd98642b032","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions (rollback matrix paragraph) and Risks and Mitigations (Downgrade first-compaction omission) and AC line: 'Recorded or inferred values survive normal compaction...'","norm_id":"na05e5ab66024f5b2","priority":0.1237,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An operator downgrades the binary after the new-code SNAPSHOT is written; the old binary reads the SNAPSHOT without creation_channel and may fail validation or silently produce a corrupt state if its schema enforcer is strict about unexpected keys or required fields.","A compaction-pause violation leaves a mixed log; before compensating-forward re-upgrade, operators need to know whether the system is safe to continue serving reads — the plan does not assert this.","A future schema enforcement tightening on the old binary could make the post-rollback state non-recoverable without the explicitly described rebuild step."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In the rollback matrix, add a paragraph such as: 'Post-rollback schema state: the old binary ignores unknown keys in SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state (verify via [existing permissive-key test or add one]); SNAPSHOTs written by the old binary omit creation_channel but are schema-valid under the old ticket_state schema; CREATEs retain the field untouched. The system serves reads correctly under the old binary in this mixed state. Compensating-forward rebuild is required only if the compaction pause was violated; until rebuild completes, affected tickets report unknown for creation_channel under both old and new readers.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Relocate the legacy Jira inference decision rule from `inbound_translate._event_meta` to the reducer's `process_create` (in `_processors.py`), which is the actual replay site where CREATE event data is inspected and projected into compiled state — following the existing `source_*` present-only pattern on lines 182-185.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["inbound_translate._event_meta (lines 158-168): def _event_meta() -> tuple[int, str, str, str]: 'Return (timestamp_ns, uuid4_str, env_id, author) for a new event.' — a write-path helper, never called during replay.","_write_event_file (inbound_translate.py lines 214-250) calls _event_meta() to compose NEW inbound events; it is not involved in reducing historical events.","process_create in _processors.py (lines 105-199) is the actual reducer function that handles CREATE events and projects data into compiled state — the existing source_* inference (lines 182-185) lives there, not in inbound_translate.","The plan says 'the reducer imports the same symbols normally' — this implies the inference logic executes in the reducer, but the decision rule placement in _event_meta contradicts that."],"finding":"The legacy Jira inference decision rule is mis-assigned to inbound_translate._event_meta, which is a write-path helper (it produces timestamp/uuid/env_id/author for NEW events), not a reducer/projection function. Historical CREATE inference must fire during reduce/replay (in process_create), not during event writing. The plan's instruction 'inbound_translate._event_meta performs the absolute package import (from rebar.reducer._version import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID) inside its function body' would place the inference code in a function that is never called during replay, making the historical Jira projection inoperative.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd58fad85523fa23c","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section: 'inbound_translate._event_meta performs the absolute package import... inside its function body, following the module's established late-import pattern, and the reducer imports the same symbols normally.'","norm_id":"n70230832dd4f7e2b","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementor following the plan literally adds the three-signal predicate inside _event_meta. Historical Jira tickets reduce without creation_channel='jira' because _event_meta is never called during reduce_ticket/replay.","The 'reducer imports the same symbols normally' note creates further ambiguity: if the reducer also imports LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR/LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID, where exactly in the reducer does it use them? The plan says _event_meta is the site, but _event_meta is not part of the reducer."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In the Architecture Decisions section, replace 'inbound_translate._event_meta performs the absolute package import (from rebar.reducer._version import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID) inside its function body, following the module's established late-import pattern' with: 'reducer/_processors.py:process_create imports LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR and LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID from rebar.reducer._version and applies the three-signal predicate to the CREATE event's stored author/env_id fields and ticket_id, projecting creation_channel=\"jira\" with creation_channel_inferred=True — following the established source_* present-only pattern on lines 182-185.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify explicitly whether `create_core`'s `creation_channel` parameter is required (no default, caller must pass) or has a sentinel default (e.g., `None` that raises at validation time with a descriptive error), and document what happens when an internal caller omits it.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan states: 'New writes always record a concrete non-unknown value.' and 'unknown is reserved for historical compatibility and is rejected for new live writes' (from child story 6fe2).","Plan states create_core will 'require an internal keyword-only concrete channel' — but does not state the Python signature (e.g., creation_channel: str vs creation_channel: str = ...). If it's a required parameter, any call site that omits it is a TypeError (good). If it has any default, the plan doesn't say what it is.","ABSENCE: No specification of the error type, error message, or default value when create_core is called without creation_channel.","create_core currently has no such parameter (confirmed by reading _commands/composer.py lines 73-191) — the full signature change is unspecified in terms of whether it's required or has a default."],"finding":"The fallback behavior when create_core is invoked without a creation_channel argument is not specified. The plan says 'New writes always record a concrete non-unknown value' and 'create_core will require an internal keyword-only concrete channel' and 'the core does not inspect the call stack' — but it is silent on whether an omitted argument raises TypeError, defaults to 'unknown', or something else. Since unknown is in the closed enum but forbidden for new writes, this creates an implementable ambiguity for the required parameter semantics.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f880fbd326e934d41","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section: 'Every live producer declares its channel at its entry boundary. Local create_core callers plus the direct Jira CREATE seam use the shared runtime validator before writing; the core does not inspect the call stack.'","norm_id":"n62b54607831ac3fe","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An implementor adds creation_channel with a default of 'python' — internal automation that bypasses the library facade (e.g., test harnesses calling create_core directly) would be silently mis-attributed as python.","An implementor makes it required with no default — any existing internal caller omitting it (e.g., a test helper) gets an untrapped TypeError rather than a descriptive error."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"4134d2c4ab5564be","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":280.2,"llm_calls":23,"llm_ms":671875.3,"total_ms":672309.9,"verify_requests":21},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"jira-reb-977","ticket_type":"epic","verdict":"BLOCK","verified_at_sha":"faa40e7b07b1ebfd7f0a12e122e9017b0cdd0b35"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784266703309823001,"uuid":"8a965483-c55e-43c9-a28b-c12f8cd33c06"}